\begin{wideslide}{Node example}
The binding energy in the liquid drop model consists of the following parts:
\begin{itemize}[type=0]
\item<3-> the \rnode{b}{surface term,} \item<2-> the \rnode{a}{volume term,}
\item[]% only dummy
\end{itemize}
\[E =
  \onslide{2-}{\rnode[t]{ae}{\pBox{darkyellow}{a_vA}} +}
  \onslide{3-}{\rnode[t]{be}{\pBox{lightgray}{-a_fA^{2/3}}} +}
  \onslide{4-}{\rnode[t]{ce}{\pBox{green}{-a_c\frac{Z(Z-1)}{A^{1/3}}}} +}
  \onslide{5-}{\rnode[t]{de}{\pBox{cyan}{-a_s\frac{(A-2Z)^2}{A}}} +}
  \onslide{6-}{\rnode[t]{ee}{\pBox{yellow}{E_p}}}
\]
\medskip
\begin{itemize}[type=0]
\item<4-> the \rnode{c}{Coulomb term,} \item<5-> the \rnode{d}{asymmetry term,}
\item<6-> and a \rnode{e}{pairing term.}
\end{itemize}
